Hi @airthomas!

This fork of tablesorter uses an alphanumeric sort by default. If you want a plain text sort, you'll need to set the [`textSorter` option](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#textsorter) as well ([demo](http://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/eY8uH/1526/)):

```js
$(function() {
  $("table").tablesorter({
    headers: {
      0: {
        sorter: 'text'
      }
    },
    textSorter: $.tablesorter.sortText
  });
});
```

@rchaput thanks for this.  I really like the idea behind this module it's a nice bit of fun.

I think we'll need to do a bit of work to clean things up,  I'm not sure making wrappers for `Py3.log()` etc adds much and also by convention private methods/vars start with a single underscore not two.

also we avoid using `subprocess` where we can in favour of the Py3 helpers.  You shouldn't be using `__init__()` etc.  But these are all things we can fixup.  The main thing is to simplify stuff as much as we can and reduce the amount of code we need to read/maintain.

